No known issues.

Fixed in v1.6.0:
- Nmap and fping commands failed on Windows (backslash paths destroyed by escapeshellcmd)
- Nmap scans appeared stuck (progress showed alive count instead of total scanned)
- Scan completion not detected in the UI for fast-finishing scans
- Nmap scan completion flickered through 4-5 refreshes before dashboard appeared
- Live scan feed flooded with hundreds of "no response" entries from nmap
- Crashed or stale scans could block future scans indefinitely
- Missing tenant_id column on sections table for existing installs
- DHCP scope monitoring crash (missing SNMP library)
- DHCP scope save accepted invalid form values (missing FILTER_VALIDATE_INT)
- License check redeclare fatal error
- Subnet save crash on Windows/IIS ("Column 'parent_id' cannot be null")
- Settings page crash when Thold plugin not installed (plugin_notification_lists table missing)
- Scan command preview mangled on Windows (backslashes and parentheses stripped from paths)

New in v1.6.0:
- Nmap scan method (-sn ping scan) for high-confidence host discovery
- Dashboard-style visual scan results with stat cards and method details
- Running scan detection on page load
- Force clear button for stuck/crashed scans
- Smart conflict detection routing (background for manual scans, inline for scheduled)
- DHCP poll debug logging for OID resolution troubleshooting
